The paper deals with the problem of recovering low-rank matrices from sampled measurements, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. The approach is based on leveraging the low-rank structure of the matrices on graphs, which suggests that the paper could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper introduces a Restricted Isometry Property (RIP) condition for efficient sampling, which could make it relevant to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper presents several efficient and parallel decoders, which could make it relevant to the sub-category of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
